      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Cook or Conserve? A Van Life Power Decision Guide for Electric Cooking Days&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;cook-or-conserve-a-van-life-power-decision-guide-for-electric-cooking-days&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#cook-or-conserve-a-van-life-power-decision-guide-for-electric-cooking-days&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Electric cooking is not just a load decision. It is a recovery decision. The question is not only “can I cook now?” The real question is &lt;strong&gt;“what does this cost my stability tomorrow?”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
