      <guid>http://localhost:1313/what-700wh-actually-runs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What 700Wh Actually Runs in Van Life (and Why It Depends)&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-700wh-actually-runs-in-van-life-and-why-it-depends&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-700wh-actually-runs-in-van-life-and-why-it-depends&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A 700Wh power station is a useful baseline, not a guarantee. In real van life, weather and routine change outcomes fast. Heat, humidity, and cloudy stretches can make the same setup feel stable one week and tight the next.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
